# Page Template: Dashboard

This template describes the structure, data flow, and component breakdown for a **dashboard page** in {{ display_name }}. Use it as a reference when building any overview or list-based page.

---

## Purpose

A dashboard page provides an at-a-glance view of key metrics and a primary list of entities. It is the first thing a user sees after login. It must load fast and communicate the most important information without requiring user interaction.

---

## Data Flow

```
Symfony API                Next.js Server Component        Browser
──────────                 ──────────────────────          ───────

GET /api/stats       ─►   DashboardPage (async)
GET /api/users?perPage=5  (fetches in parallel)
                     ◄─   renders HTML with data

                                                    ─►   Page arrives
                                                         with data already
                                                         present (no spinner)

                                                         <UserTable> is a
                                                         Client Component -
                                                         handles sort/filter
                                                         interactions
```

Both API calls happen in the Server Component using `Promise.all`. The browser receives a fully rendered HTML page - no loading spinners on the initial paint.

---

## URL

```
/dashboard
```

Protected route - requires authentication. Redirect to `/login` if unauthenticated.

