## Component Breakdown

| Component | Type | Responsibility |
|-----------|------|----------------|
| `DashboardPage` | Server Component | Fetch data, pass to children |
| `StatsRow` | Server Component | Render metric cards (no interactivity) |
| `MetricCard` | Server Component | Single stat (label + number + trend) |
| `DataTable` | **Client Component** | Sort, filter, pagination interactions |
| `TableRow` | Server Component | Render a single row (no state) |
| `ActionMenu` | **Client Component** | Dropdown actions per row |
| `SearchInput` | **Client Component** | Controlled search input with debounce |
| `Pagination` | **Client Component** | Page change triggers router.push |

The rule: if a component needs `useState`, `useEffect`, or an event handler, it is a Client Component. Everything else is a Server Component.

---

## Server Component Implementation

```typescript
// apps/web/src/app/(dashboard)/dashboard/page.tsx

import { Suspense } from 'react';
import { getStats } from '@/services/stats';
import { getUsers } from '@/services/users';
import { StatsRow } from '@/components/features/dashboard/StatsRow';
import { DataTable } from '@/components/features/dashboard/DataTable';

interface DashboardPageProps {
  searchParams: { page?: string; search?: string };
}

export default async function DashboardPage({ searchParams }: DashboardPageProps) {
  const page = Number(searchParams.page ?? 1);
  const search = searchParams.search ?? '';

  // Parallel data fetching - both requests fire simultaneously
  const [stats, usersPage] = await Promise.all([
    getStats(),
    getUsers({ page, search, perPage: 20 }),
  ]);

  return (
    <main className="space-y-8 p-6">
      <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Dashboard</h1>
        <a href="/dashboard/new" className="btn btn-primary">
          New Item
        </a>
      </div>

      {/* Stats are static - no Suspense needed, they are fetched above */}
      <StatsRow stats={stats} />

      {/* DataTable is a Client Component but its initial data comes from the server */}
      <DataTable
        initialData={usersPage.data}
        meta={usersPage.meta}
        currentPage={page}
        currentSearch={search}
      />
    </main>
  );
}

export const metadata = {
  title: 'Dashboard - {{ display_name }}',
};
```

